==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Firkin
<hw>Fir"kin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From AS.
<ets>fe⟦oacute⟧wer</ets> four (or an allied word, perh. Dutch or Danish)
+ <ets>-kin</ets>. See <er>Four</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A varying
measure of capacity, usually being the fourth part of a barrel;
specifically, a measure equal to nine imperial gallons.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small wooden vessel or cask of indeterminate size,
-- used for butter, lard, etc.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Firlot</ent>⟦br⟧
